class Solution {
    public int reachNumber(int target) {
        target = Math.abs(target);
        int k = 0;
        long sum = 0;
        while (sum < target) {
            k++;
            sum += k;
        }
        if ((sum - target) % 2 == 0) {
            return k;
        } else if ((sum + k + 1 - target) % 2 == 0) {
            return k + 1;
        } else {
            return k + 2;
        }
    }
}
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(sqrt(|target|))
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: The key insight is that the sum of the first k moves is S = k(k+1)/2. We need S ≥ |target| and S-|target| even so we can flip the sign of some move to cancel the excess. The loop finds the smallest k with S ≥ |target|. If S-|target| is even we are done; otherwise we need one or two more moves to make the difference even.

